<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph box="[7,914,1349,1807]" pageId="24" pageNumber="277" type="mainText">
Small shrub. Leaves alternate, stiff. Flowers in the axils of bracts, subtended by leaf-like bracteoles, these overtopping the flowers; flowers bisexual; perianth 5-lobed, the lobes with a wing-like outgrowth below the middle in fruit; stamens 5, alternating with the semi-orbicular lobes of the hypogynous disk; anthers with appendages sagittately split to the base. Seeds horizontal, rarely vertical, occupying only the lower part of the fruit. One sp., 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Rhaphidophyton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="24" pageNumber="277" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="regelii">
R. regelii 
<authority>(Bunge) Iljin</authority>
</taxonomicName>
, C Asia.
</paragraph>
